Description:
CD-10 code O99 is a category for maternal conditions that complicate pregnancy, childbirth, and the period after birth. 
This category includes various subcategories for different types of diseases, such as those affecting the blood, immune system, endocrine system, mental health, nervous system, and others. 
Specific examples include anemia 
(O99.0), other blood/immune diseases 
(O99.1), endocrine/nutritional/metabolic diseases 
(O99.2), mental and nervous system disorders 
(O99.3), circulatory diseases 
(O99.4), respiratory diseases 
(O99.5), digestive diseases
(O99.6), skin and subcutaneous tissue diseases 
(O99.7), and other specified conditions 
(O99.8). Other specified diseases and conditions complicating pregnancy, childbirth and the puerperium
